; Condition tested in a DEEPER induction than the cycle that sets it.
; Two chained inductions (cf. two_inductions.dr): reach1 is the outer
; cycle; the condition `gate` is derived from reach1's output (so its
; setter sits alongside the outer cycle), and the inner induction
; reach2's recursive rule tests `gate`. The driver exercises three
; arrival orders of the gate relative to the inner induction's data:
; inner data before the gate opens (stalls, then unleashes), the
; gate-opening tuple in the same batch as fresh outer-cycle data, and
; inner data after the gate is already open.

#message base(i32 A).
#message edge1(i32 A, i32 B).
#message edge2(i32 A, i32 B).
#message marker(i32 M).

#local reach1(i32 A).
reach1(A) : base(A).
reach1(B) : reach1(A), edge1(A, B).

gate : reach1(M), marker(M).

#local reach2(i32 A).
reach2(A) : reach1(A).
reach2(B) : reach2(A), edge2(A, B), gate.

#query out(bound i32 A).
out(A) : reach2(A).
